MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 146}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 5f7201a12d95ffc409449d95f23cf332, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 0
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_FontData:
    m_Font: {fileID: 12800000, guid: 792fb289b1637474daa5113717db16c7, type: 3}
    m_FontSize: 25
    m_FontStyle: 0
    m_BestFit: 0
    m_MinSize: 23
    m_MaxSize: 25
    m_Alignment: 0
    m_AlignByGeometry: 0
    m_RichText: 1
    m_HorizontalOverflow: 0
    m_VerticalOverflow: 0
    m_LineSpacing: 1
  m_Text: 'This game is played with 15 numbered object balls and the cue ball. The
    object balls are divided into two groups, the Solids (containing balls 1 through
    7) and the Striped (containing balls 9 through 15). the 8-ball does not belong
    to any group. The aim is to legally pocket all balls of a particular group assigned
    to a player and then legally pocket the 8-ball. The first player to legally pocket
    an object ball after the break shot is assigned to that group of balls. Balls
    pocketed in the break shot are not used to assign groups.


    To legally break,
    the cue ball must be shot from behind the Head String. Also, at least one object
    ball must be pocketed or 4 numbered balls must hit the rail or else the player
    breaks again after re-racking. If the 8-ball is pocketed on the break, the player
    breaks again after re-racking.


    After the groups have been assigned, failure
    to contact a ball belonging to the player''s group is a foul. Failure to pocket
    any numbered ball or drive any ball to the rail is also a foul. Pocketing the
    cue ball (which is called a scratch) is also a foul. Every foul after break results
    in incoming player having ball in hand anywhere on the table.


    To win the
    game, the player has to legally pocket the 8-ball after all of that player''s
    object balls have been pocketed. If the player commits a scratch while pocketing
    the 8-ball, it results in a loss of game.'
