--- !u!114 &3941
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 653}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 5f7201a12d95ffc409449d95f23cf332, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 0
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_FontData:
    m_Font: {fileID: 12800000, guid: 792fb289b1637474daa5113717db16c7, type: 3}
    m_FontSize: 25
    m_FontStyle: 0
    m_BestFit: 0
    m_MinSize: 2
    m_MaxSize: 40
    m_Alignment: 0
    m_AlignByGeometry: 0
    m_RichText: 1
    m_HorizontalOverflow: 0
    m_VerticalOverflow: 0
    m_LineSpacing: 1
  m_Text: 'This game is played with 15 red balls (called Reds), 6 balls of other
    colors (called Colors) and a white cue ball. Your goal is to pocket (pot) the
    balls in a legal manner and score more points than your opponent.


    The points
    assigned to the balls are as follows:

    - Red: 1 point

    - Yellow: 2 points

    -
    Green: 3 points

    - Brown: 4 points

    - Blue: 5 points

    - Pink: 6 points

    -
    Black: 7 points


    If fouls are committed, the opponent gets the points. Not
    hitting the target ball "on" first is the most common foul.


    While there
    are Reds on the table, you have to strike and pocket the Reds at every start
    of your turn. If you pocket a Red, your turn continues and you then have to pocket
    one of the Colors that you strike. If you legally pocket a Color, your turn continues
    and you go back to pocketting a Red. If you do not pocket a ball, you lose your
    turn.


    While there are Reds on the table, any Color that is pocketed will
    be "Spotted" on the table (i.e. returned on the table to its original position).
    Any Red that is pocketed will never be spotted.


    Once all Reds are off the
    table, the Colors will have to be pocketed in the following order: Yellow, Green,
    Brown, Blue, Pink, Black. Any Color illegally pocketed will be spotted on the
    table. Any Color legally pocketed will remain off the table.


    When only
    the Black is left on the table, the next player that pockets it or commits a
    foul will end the "Frame". The player with most points wins the frame.'
--- !u!114 &3942
